## Phase 3 — File API MVP

### Goal

Expose structured file operations so agents and SDK consumers do not need a local filesystem.

### Endpoints

```http
GET    /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/tree?path=...
GET    /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/files?path=...
PUT    /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/files?path=...
PATCH  /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/files?path=...
DELETE /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/files?path=...
POST   /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/search
GET    /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/status
GET    /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/diff
POST   /api/v1/workspaces/:workspace_id/commit
```

### SDK Tool Mapping

```text
repo.list(path)      -> GET tree
repo.read(path)      -> GET files
repo.search(...)     -> POST search
repo.write(...)      -> PUT files
repo.patch(...)      -> PATCH files
repo.delete(...)     -> DELETE files
repo.status()        -> GET status
repo.diff()          -> GET diff
repo.commit(...)     -> POST commit
```

### File Read Response

```json
{
  "path": "src/content/knowledge/example.mdx",
  "encoding": "utf8",
  "content": "---\ntitle: Example\n---\n\nBody...",
  "stat": {
    "size": 1234,
    "mtime": "..."
  }
}
```

### Patch Request

Support unified diffs for MVP.

```json
{
  "patch": "--- a/src/content/example.mdx\n+++ b/src/content/example.mdx\n@@ ...",
  "expectedSha": "optional_blob_sha"
}
```

### Commit Request

```json
{
  "message": "Update onboarding knowledge note",
  "author": {
    "name": "TreeSeed Agent",
    "email": "agent@example.invalid"
  },
  "indexPolicy": "incremental"
}
```

### Commit Response

```json
{
  "repoId": "repo_...",
  "workspaceId": "ws_...",
  "branchName": "agent/demo-task",
  "commitSha": "abc123...",
  "changedPaths": ["src/content/knowledge/example.mdx"],
  "status": "committed"
}
```

### Safety Rules

* Enforce allowed path globs on every operation.
* Block `.git/**`, environment files, secrets, lockfiles, or generated directories unless explicitly allowed.
* Normalize paths and reject path traversal.
* Limit max file size for read/write.
* Limit search output.
* Diff before commit must be inspectable.
* Commit must produce audit event.

### Verification

Tests:

* list root tree
* read file
* write new file
* patch existing file
* delete file
* search text
* status shows changes
* diff shows changes
* commit returns changed paths and SHA
* path traversal rejected
* disallowed path rejected

### Deliverables

* Structured file API
* Search MVP using `rg` or Elixir file scan
* Commit API
* Audit events for all mutations

### Exit Criteria

* An agent can modify repository content without a local clone.
* TreeDB can commit those changes efficiently.

