### Rust Introduction Point

Create `crates/treedb_graph` when:

1. The Elixir graph contract is stable.
2. Fixture indexing tests exist.
3. Performance bottlenecks are measurable.

Initial Rust functions:

```text
parse_markdown_document(input) -> document structure
extract_sections(input) -> sections
extract_links(input) -> links
rank_nodes(query, candidates) -> scored candidates
compute_changed_graph_nodes(changed_paths) -> affected node IDs
```

Use Rust NIFs only for bounded CPU-heavy operations. Do not run shell or Git commands inside Rust NIFs.

### Context Pack MVP

A context pack response should include:

```text
