### AgentSdk Integration Pattern

Prefer preserving existing public methods.

```ts
const sdk = new AgentSdk({
  // existing options
  treeDb: {
    baseUrl: process.env.TREEDB_URL!,
    token: process.env.TREEDB_TOKEN,
    repoId: process.env.TREEDB_REPO_ID,
    actor: {
      id: "agent_demo",
      type: "agent",
      teamId: "team_demo"
    }
  }
});
```

Existing-style calls should route to TreeDB when configured:

```ts
await sdk.search({ model: "knowledge", query: "release provenance" });
await sdk.get({ model: "decision", id: "decision:..." });
await sdk.update({ model: "note", id, data });
await sdk.refreshGraph();
await sdk.queryGraph({ query: "approved decisions feeding releases" });
await sdk.buildContextPack({ query: "market package provenance" });
```

### Adapter Strategy

Define ports inside the SDK first:

```ts
interface RepositoryPort {
  createWorkspace(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  listTree(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  readFile(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  writeFile(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  patchFile(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  status(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  diff(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  commit(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  exec(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
}

interface ContentPort {
  get(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  search(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  create(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  update(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  delete(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
}

interface GraphPort {
  refresh(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  query(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
  buildContextPack(input: unknown): Promise<unknown>;
}
```

Implement:

```text
LocalRepositoryPort -> existing SDK filesystem/Git code
TreeDbRepositoryPort -> TreeDbClient
LocalContentPort -> existing ContentStore
TreeDbContentPort -> TreeDbClient content endpoints
LocalGraphPort -> existing ContentGraphRuntime
TreeDbGraphPort -> TreeDbClient graph endpoints
```

This lets TreeDB integrate without destabilizing existing local mode.

### SDK Verification

Add tests:

* TreeDbClient request construction.
* TreeDbClient error handling.
* Adapter maps SDK search/get/update to TreeDB requests.
* Local mode remains unchanged.
* Remote mode can run against a mocked TreeDB server.
* Contract tests run against the real Phoenix app in CI/dev.

### Deliverables

* TreeDbClient
* SDK types
* Adapter ports
* Local and remote implementation wiring
* Tests
* Usage docs

### Exit Criteria

* SDK users can opt into TreeDB mode.
* Existing local SDK tests still pass.
