## Final MVP Definition

TreeDB MVP is complete when:

1. A large content repository can remain on a TreeDB volume.
2. A stateless worker can update repository files through the TypeScript SDK without cloning the repository.
3. TreeDB creates a Git commit with changed paths and audit events.
4. Agents can explore the repository through structured file/search APIs.
5. Agents can run constrained remote shell commands when necessary.
6. TreeDB can build a basic graph index and context pack for Markdown/MDX content.
7. SDK local mode and TreeDB remote mode can both pass integration tests against the same fixture.
8. The architecture remains aligned with TreeSeed’s human-governed workflow: agents help, humans approve, releases explain what changed and why, and shared outputs preserve provenance.

